//! Translated from `src/nvim/option_vars.h`, plus the option-specific
//! bit-flag enums and string-value-set arrays from
//! `option_vars.generated.h` (generated by `src/gen/gen_options.lua`
//! from `src/options.lua`'s master option table - translated directly
//! from a pre-built copy of that generated file found in this
//! checkout's own `build/src/nvim/auto/option_vars.generated.h`,
//! matching this project's "translate the generator's output directly"
//! convention for codegen-derived content, same as how
//! `ex_cmds_defs.rs`'s deferred `cmdidx_T` will eventually be handled).
//!
//! Translated: every one of the header's 337 `EXTERN`/`extern` global
//! option-value variables (as a single [`OptionVars`] struct, mirroring
//! `globals.rs`'s own `Globals` struct for the exact same "one flat
//! process-wide mutable state bag, reachable from any function with no
//! parameter" reason - see that file's module doc comment), the 20
//! option-specific bit-flag enums (as `pub mod` bit-flag constant groups,
//! matching `HL_*`/`MarkMoveRes` elsewhere in this crate, since they
//! combine via bitwise OR rather than being mutually exclusive
//! variants), the ~45 `opt_*_values` valid-string-value arrays, and the
//! smaller standalone character/string constant groups (`CPO_*`, `WW_*`,
//! `MOUSE_*`, `SHM_*`, `GO_*`, `COM_*`, `BS_*`, etc.).
//!
//! `empty_string_option` is translated as a plain constant (not an
//! `OptionVars` field): its only purpose in the original is "a non-NULL
//! sentinel so `char *` option fields never need a NULL check" - this
//! crate already represents nullable string options as `Option<Vec<u8>>`
//! throughout, which makes that sentinel trick structurally unnecessary,
//! but the constant is kept for direct traceability back to the source.

use crate::sign_defs::SIGN_SHOW_MAX;
